Launch an OmniScript from a FlexCard 

Launch an Angular or LWC OmniScript from an OmniScript Action element on a FlexCard. For example, launch a form that updates Account information based on the account Id passed from the FlexCard to the OmniScript.

From the FlexCard Designer, drag an Action element into a state.
Select OmniScript from the Action Type dropdown. 
Click into OmniScript and select the OmniScript to launch.
In the ContextId field, enter the sObject's context Id associated with your OmniScript.
To pass contextual data as a key/value pair, click + Add New next to Input Parameters, and perform the following tasks:
Enter a variable name in the Key field. Prefix your variable name with c__, such as c__name.
Enter the variable value in the Value field.

(Optional) Select whether to open the OmniScript in the current tab or a new tab, select from the Open Target In dropdown.
Whatâ€™s next: To style your action element, click Style to open the Style panel.
title: Launch an OmniScript from a FlexCard
